Pre-Game Insights: The Ukrainian team will have the return of its starting player Mykhailo Mudryk after an injury.
Both teams will try to rehabilitate themselves in the eyes of their fans after unsuccessful first matches.
Bookmakers consider the Czech national team to be the favourite of the match and give high odds for a draw.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will take place in Prague at the Eden Stadium on 10 September at 21:45.
The match will be broadcast by regional channels Suspilne and the MEGOGO platform.
Given the presence of many Ukrainian fans, we should expect a lot of support for the team.
